quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  39,53,"Say, \"O my servants! Who have acted extravagantly (transgressed) against their own souls, do not despair of the mercy of Allah; surely Allah forgives all faults; surely He is the Forgiving the Merciful"
  39,54,And return to your Lord time after time and submit to Him before there come unto you the punishment when you cannot be helped
  39,55,And follow the best of that which has been revealed to you from your Lord before the punishment comes suddenly while you do not even perceive
  39,56,"Lest a soul should say, \"O woe to me! For what I fell short of my duty to Allah, and I was indeed among the scoffers"
  39,57,"Or should say, \"Had Allah guided me, I would certainly have been of those who are dutiful"
  39,58,"Or should say when it sees the punishment, \"O, if I only had another chance that I might be among the righteous"
  39,59,"(But the answer will be,) \"Nay! For My revelations came to you, but you rejected them, and were haughty and you were among the unbelievers"
  39,60,And on the Day of Resurrection you shall see those who lied against Allah; their faces shall be blackened. Is there not in hell an abode for the haughty
  39,61,"And Allah shall deliver those who guard (against evil) with their achievement; evil shall not touch them, nor shall they grieve"
  39,62,Allah is the Creator of all things and He is the Guardian and Disposer of all things
  39,63,"His are the keys of the heavens and the earth; and those who disbelieve in the revelations of Allah, these it is that are the losers"
  39,64,"Say, \"What! Do you then bid me serve others than Allah, O you ignorant (or stupid) ones"
  39,65,"And certainly, it has been revealed to you and to those before you, \"Surely if you ascribe partners (with Allah), your work would certainly come to naught and you would certainly be of the losers"
  39,66,Nay! But serve Allah alone and be of the thankful
  39,67,"And they have not honoured Allah with the honour that is due to Him; and the whole earth shall be in His grip on the Day of Resurrection and the heavens rolled up in His right hand; Glorified is He, and High Exalted above all that they ascribe as partners"
  39,68,"And the trumpet shall be blown, and all those that are in the heavens and all those that are in the earth shall swoon away (or become unconscious), except such as Allah wills; then it shall be blown again, then lo! They shall stand up waiting"
  39,69,"And the earth shall beam with the light of its Lord, and the Book (Record) shall be laid open, and the prophets and the witnesses shall be brought up, and judgment shall be given between them with justice, and they shall not be dealt with unjustly"
  39,70,"And every soul shall be paid back full for what it has done, and He knows best what they do"
  39,71,"And those who disbelieve shall be driven to hell in companies; until, when they come to it, its doors shall be opened, and the keepers of it shall say to them, \"Did not there come to you messengers of your own, reciting to you the revelations (or com)"
  39,72,"It shall be said, \"Enter the gates of hell to abide therein; so evil is the abode of the haughty"
  39,73,"And those who are careful of (their duty to) their Lord shall be conveyed to the Garden in companies; until when they come to it, and its doors are opened, the keepers of it shall say to them, \"Peace be on you, you have done well; therefore enter in"
  39,74,"And they shall say, \"All praise is due to Allah, Who has made good to us His promise, and He has given us this land as a heritage; we may dwell in the Garden where we please; so goodly is the reward of the workers"
  39,75,"And you shall see the angels going round about the throne glorifying the praise of their Lord; and judgment shall be given between them with justice, and it shall be said, \"All praise is due to Allah, the Lord of the worlds"